<div class="mf-hero"><div class="mf-hero__overlay"></div><div class="mf-hero__content"><div class="mf-hero__label">Educational Resource</div><h1>Understanding <em>Male Infertility</em></h1><p class="mf-hero__sub">LogixX Fertility provides clinically proven diagnostics and treatments to support you and your partner on your journey to conceive.</p><div class="mf-hero__pills"><div class="mf-hero__pill">Clinically Proven</div><div class="mf-hero__pill">Expert Guidance</div><div class="mf-hero__pill">Advanced Diagnostics</div></div><div class="mf-hero__stats"><div class="mf-hero__stat"><span class="mf-hero__stat-num">1 in 7</span><span class="mf-hero__stat-lbl">UK Couples</span></div><div class="mf-hero__stat-div"></div><div class="mf-hero__stat"><span class="mf-hero__stat-num">50%</span><span class="mf-hero__stat-lbl">Male Factor</span></div><div class="mf-hero__stat-div"></div><div class="mf-hero__stat"><span class="mf-hero__stat-num">85%</span><span class="mf-hero__stat-lbl">Conceive Naturally</span></div></div></div></div><div class="mf-stats"><div class="mf-stat"><div class="mf-stat__icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M17 21v-2a4 4 0 00-4-4H5a4 4 0 00-4 4v2"></path><circle cx="9" cy="7" r="4"></circle><path d="M23 21v-2a4 4 0 00-3-3.87"></path><path d="M16 3.13a4 4 0 010 7.75"></path></svg></div><div class="mf-stat__num">1 in 7</div><div class="mf-stat__label">UK Couples Affected</div><div class="mf-stat__sub">Approximately 3.5 million people in the UK are unable to have a child</div></div><div class="mf-stat"><div class="mf-stat__icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"></circle><line x1="12" y1="8" x2="12" y2="12"></line><line x1="12" y1="16" x2="12.01" y2="16"></line></svg></div><div class="mf-stat__num">50%</div><div class="mf-stat__label">Male Factor</div><div class="mf-stat__sub">In 50% of cases the problem lies wholly or partly with the male partner</div></div><div class="mf-stat"><div class="mf-stat__icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M22 11.08V12a10 10 0 11-5.93-9.14"></path><polyline points="22 4 12 14.01 9 11.01"></polyline></svg></div><div class="mf-stat__num">85%</div><div class="mf-stat__label">Conceive Naturally</div><div class="mf-stat__sub">Many couples conceive whilst undergoing investigations within the first year</div></div></div><div class="mf-section"><div class="mf-section-header"><div class="mf-section-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"></circle><line x1="12" y1="8" x2="12" y2="12"></line><line x1="12" y1="16" x2="12.01" y2="16"></line></svg></div><h2>When Should I Seek Help?</h2></div><div class="mf-card"><p>If you have been trying unsuccessfully to produce a pregnancy for <strong>1-2 years without using contraception</strong>, you should contact your GP for further advice.</p><p>Your GP will normally wish to review you and your partner together. Urological investigations are essential in revealing reversible underlying causes for male-factor subfertility.</p></div><div class="mf-note"><strong>Important:</strong> Not all advanced tests are available on the NHS such as Sperm Oxidative Stress tests or Sperm DNA Fragmentation tests. Current NICE guidance may not reflect current advances available in the private sector.</div></div><div class="mf-section"><div class="mf-section-header"><div class="mf-section-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M10.29 3.86L1.82 18a2 2 0 001.71 3h16.94a2 2 0 001.71-3L13.71 3.86a2 2 0 00-3.42 0z"></path><line x1="12" y1="9" x2="12" y2="13"></line><line x1="12" y1="17" x2="12.01" y2="17"></line></svg></div><h2>Causes of Male Infertility</h2></div><div class="mf-card"><p>In <strong>75% of infertile men</strong>, the cause remains unexplained. It may still be possible for couples to conceive naturally, provided some sperm are present.</p></div><div class="mf-grid2"><div class="mf-cause-card"><div class="mf-cause-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M18 8h1a4 4 0 010 8h-1"></path><path d="M2 8h16v9a4 4 0 01-4 4H6a4 4 0 01-4-4V8z"></path></svg></div><h4>Lifestyle Factors</h4><p>Smoking, excessive alcohol, recreational drugs, gym supplements and excessive heat from saunas and hot baths</p></div><div class="mf-cause-card"><div class="mf-cause-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M22 12h-4l-3 9L9 3l-3 9H2"></path></svg></div><h4>Hormonal Issues</h4><p>Imbalances in thyroid, prolactin, FSH, LH or testosterone including pituitary disease and hypothalamic conditions</p></div><div class="mf-cause-card"><div class="mf-cause-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"></circle><path d="M8 14s1.5 2 4 2 4-2 4-2"></path><line x1="9" y1="9" x2="9.01" y2="9"></line><line x1="15" y1="9" x2="15.01" y2="9"></line></svg></div><h4>Physical Causes</h4><p>Varicocele, previous testicular infection or surgery, undescended testis, obstruction of sperm transport</p></div><div class="mf-cause-card"><div class="mf-cause-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M21 16V8a2 2 0 00-1-1.73l-7-4a2 2 0 00-2 0l-7 4A2 2 0 002 8v8a2 2 0 001 1.73l7 4a2 2 0 002 0l7-4A2 2 0 0021 16z"></path></svg></div><h4>Genetic Factors</h4><p>Chromosomal abnormalities such as Klinefelter's syndrome and Y chromosome micro-deletions</p></div></div></div><div class="mf-section"><div class="mf-section-header"><div class="mf-section-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><polygon points="13 2 3 14 12 14 11 22 21 10 12 10 13 2"></polygon></svg></div><h2>Sperm Oxidative Stress and DNA Fragmentation</h2></div><div class="mf-card"><p>High levels of oxidative stress can damage spermatozoa causing <strong>sperm DNA damage</strong> associated with poor sperm function. Recommended for:</p><ul class="mf-list"><li><div class="mf-list-dot"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg></div><span>Idiopathic unexplained male infertility</span></li><li><div class="mf-list-dot"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg></div><span>Male partners of recurrent pregnancy loss or history of failed IUI or IVF cycles</span></li><li><div class="mf-list-dot"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg></div><span>Infection of male accessory glands such as prostatitis</span></li><li><div class="mf-list-dot"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg></div><span>History of smoking or older males over the age of 40</span></li></ul></div><div class="mf-note"><strong>LogixX Solution:</strong> The <strong>MiOXSYS Redox System</strong> measures oxidative-reductive stress in human semen — results in under 5 minutes.</div></div><div class="mf-section"><div class="mf-section-header"><div class="mf-section-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><polyline points="22 12 18 12 15 21 9 3 6 12 2 12"></polyline></svg></div><h2>WHO Reference Values for Human Semen</h2></div><div class="mf-who-ref"><div class="mf-ref"><span class="mf-ref-val">1.5ml+</span><div class="mf-ref-label">Semen Volume</div></div><div class="mf-ref"><span class="mf-ref-val">7.2+</span><div class="mf-ref-label">pH Level</div></div><div class="mf-ref"><span class="mf-ref-val">15M/ml+</span><div class="mf-ref-label">Sperm Concentration</div></div><div class="mf-ref"><span class="mf-ref-val">39M+</span><div class="mf-ref-label">Total Sperm</div></div><div class="mf-ref"><span class="mf-ref-val">40%+</span><div class="mf-ref-label">Total Motility</div></div><div class="mf-ref"><span class="mf-ref-val">32%+</span><div class="mf-ref-label">Progressive Motility</div></div><div class="mf-ref"><span class="mf-ref-val">58%+</span><div class="mf-ref-label">Live Spermatozoa</div></div><div class="mf-ref"><span class="mf-ref-val">4%+</span><div class="mf-ref-label">Normal Morphology</div></div></div></div><div class="mf-section"><div class="mf-section-header"><div class="mf-section-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M22 11.08V12a10 10 0 11-5.93-9.14"></path><polyline points="22 4 12 14.01 9 11.01"></polyline></svg></div><h2>Treatment Options</h2></div><div class="mf-grid2"><div class="mf-treatment-card"><div class="mf-treatment-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M20.84 4.61a5.5 5.5 0 00-7.78 0L12 5.67l-1.06-1.06a5.5 5.5 0 00-7.78 7.78l1.06 1.06L12 21.23l7.78-7.78 1.06-1.06a5.5 5.5 0 000-7.78z"></path></svg></div><h4>General Lifestyle Measures</h4><p>Wear loose clothing, stop smoking, reduce alcohol. Proxeed Plus may help sperm quality over a 90-day course.</p></div><div class="mf-treatment-card"><div class="mf-treatment-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"></circle><path d="M8 14s1.5 2 4 2 4-2 4-2"></path><line x1="9" y1="9" x2="9.01" y2="9"></line><line x1="15" y1="9" x2="15.01" y2="9"></line></svg></div><h4>Varicocele Treatment</h4><p>Minimally invasive embolization or surgical ligation — 1 in 3 couples achieve natural conception.</p></div><div class="mf-treatment-card"><div class="mf-treatment-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M12 2L2 7l10 5 10-5-10-5z"></path><path d="M2 17l10 5 10-5"></path></svg></div><h4>IUI</h4><p>Most motile sperm injected through the cervix at ovulation. Approximately 7-8% pregnancy rate per cycle.</p></div><div class="mf-treatment-card"><div class="mf-treatment-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="2"></circle><path d="M12 2v4M12 18v4M4.93 4.93l2.83 2.83M16.24 16.24l2.83 2.83M2 12h4M18 12h4"></path></svg></div><h4>ICSI</h4><p>A single sperm injected directly into an egg. Approximately 30-40% pregnancy rate per cycle.</p></div><div class="mf-treatment-card"><div class="mf-treatment-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><polyline points="14.5 17.5 3 6 3 3 6 3 17.5 14.5"></polyline><line x1="13" y1="19" x2="19" y2="13"></line></svg></div><h4>Surgical Sperm Retrieval</h4><p>Sperm retrieved directly from the testicle with 100% success rate in finding sperm for as<__filter_complete__></__filter_complete__></p></div></div></div>
